{
  "message": "fuzz: expand seed corpora for repair/recovery fuzz targets\n\nStrengthen 1-seed corpora for security-critical repair/recovery paths:\n\nfuzz_repair_codec_roundtrip (was 1 seed, now 8):\n- Different block sizes (64/128/256)\n- Varying source block and repair symbol counts\n- Edge cases: no repair, full repair, offset blocks\n\nfuzz_lrc_repair (was 1 seed, now 6):\n- All LRC group sizes (2/3/4)\n- Varying global parity counts\n- Max group configuration\n\nfuzz_native_cow_recovery (was 1 seed, now 6):\n- All block size choices (64/128/256/512)\n- Varying commit and write counts\n- Random entropy seed\n\nThese seeds ensure the coverage-guided fuzzer starts from meaningful\ninputs rather than exploring from trivial single-byte seeds.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
